Ticket ID: AI-BIZ-2026-02-24-03
Title: Specification Design for Romanian Investment Tax Master File
Classification: Financial Data Architecture / AI-Assisted Specification Development
Execution Date: 24 February 2026
Status: Completed
Executive Summary
This activity consisted of designing a comprehensive specification document defining the architecture and requirements for a Romanian investment tax tracking system.
The specification acts as the master blueprint for the development of an Excel file capable of managing multiple categories of investment income and calculating the corresponding fiscal obligations.
Design Objectives
The file must:
	• calculate Romanian investment taxes accurately
	• support multi-year portfolio tracking
	• maintain transparent and traceable calculations
	• remain modular and expandable
	• support manual inputs where automation is impractical
Architecture Overview
The design includes the following modules:
	• Settings configuration
	• Foreign exchange handling
	• Stock transaction tracking
	• Dividend management
	• FIFO lot tracking engine
	• Forex trading results
	• Cryptocurrency transaction module
	• Royalties and miscellaneous income tracking
	• Loss carryforward engine
	• Tax calculation engine
	• CASS calculation logic
	• ANAF reporting summary
	• Optional dashboard
	• Documentation module
Each module was specified with clear requirements, including input fields, calculation logic, and validation rules.
Design Philosophy
Key design principles include:
	• transparency of calculations
	• absence of hidden automation
	• no unstable formulas
	• no circular references
	• clear documentation
	• manual override capabilities where required
Strategic Importance
This specification serves as the foundation for the modular development of the investment tracking system and ensures that the project progresses in a controlled and verifiable manner.
